abstract: "Seismo Framework v2.0.2 is an innovative eight-parameter assessment framework for monitoring tectonic stress evolution and forecasting earthquake probability with 3-14 day lead times. The framework integrates seismic activity, crustal deformation, hydrogeological indicators, electrical/magnetic signals, instability indicators, tectonic stress state, rock properties, and gas geochemistry using Bayesian probability updating. Validation on 120 M â‰¥ 6.0 earthquakes (2000-2020) shows 84.2% accuracy, 78.5% sensitivity, 86.7% specificity, and 0.876 ROC AUC."

